snippet.textDisplay:
Finally good to see Noori arrive in their full glory. This is such a brilliant composition bringing and showcasing the best of this talented band. Ali Noor finally returned to his element and I think for the fans and the music lovers they should stick to more songs like this one. Ali Hamza and his low octave voice is no doubt a plus and when both the brothers equally come together the band comes to life. 

The arrangement of the track was outstanding with different layers added made it memorable. The collaboration with Shilpa Rao was excellent. She did a wonderful job. More of this from Noori, less of their slow stuff, this type of songs their strength.

snippet.textDisplay: Her name is Noor Zahra Kazim, daughter of Raza Kazim, a well known lawyer of his time. Not only that, she is the mother of the Noori duo Ali Hamza and Ali Noor. The instrument she is playing is called the Sagar Veena which was invented by her own father Raza Kazim. And currently she is the only person in the world who knows how to play that instrument.
